FBIS4-6113 "dreas074__a94045" FBIS-EAS-94-074-A Daily Report 18 April 1994 ANNEX Mongolia President Consults Leaders on Resignation Demands President Consults Leaders on Resignation Demands OW1504174894 Ulaanbaatar MONTSAME in English 1439 GMT 15 Apr 94--FOR OFFICIAL USE ONLY OW1504174894 Ulaanbaatar MONTSAME English BFN [Text] Ulaanbaatar, April 15 (OANA-MONTSAME) -- The Mongolian president is going on the top consultations starting a day ago in order to overcome the opposition arising in connection with the hunger strike and other actions for resignation of the goverment carried out by the Mongolian Democratic Association (MDA) at the central square of the Mongolian capital. Particiated in the consultations are leaders of the three parliamentary parties and the Prime Minister P. Jasray. During the meeting the sides have agreed to consider the political actions for resignation of the government on the part of the MDA as a subject under discussion at the Great State Hural and make public the social position of the parliamentary parties referring to the situation shaped down through their leaders, informs the press service of the Mongolian president.
